<TITLE> Bazlur Rahman's janaza held in Sherpur</font> </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sherpur, February 27 (bdnews24.com)The first namaj-e-janaza of the late 'Sangbad' editor Bazlur Rahman was held in Sherpur at Nakla High School ground Wednesday morning. A large number of Sherpur people including politicians, cultural activists, journalists, lawyers, doctors and other professionals gathered at the janaza. Earlier, an ambulance had carried Bazlur Rahman's body and his wife former minister and AL presidium member Motia Chowdhury from Dhaka to Sherpur, where the coffin was first taken to his maternal grandfather's home in Baneshwardi village. The coffin was then carried to his sister's place in nearby Ishibpur, Nakla, to allow relatives, friends and neighbours to pay their last respects to the deceased. Prior to the janaza, Motia Chowdhury, Sherpur's AL president former MP Atiur Rahman Atik and other local leaders addressed those present. People from all walks of life laid flowers on the coffin. bdnews24
